268→// agentsMdRewritePrompt is the prompt sent to claude --print to rewrite AGENTS.md.
269→const agentsMdRewritePrompt = `You are rewriting an AGENTS.md file for a project that now uses agentsea sandboxes instead of git worktrees for agent isolation.
270→
271→REMOVE all of the following:
272→- Worktree creation/verification blocks (look for: "MANDATORY FIRST STEP", "WORKTREE ISOLATION", "WORKTREE VERIFICATION", "EnterWorktree")
273→- "never cd to main repo" / "verify CWD" rules
274→- Worktree-specific git workflow (branch naming like "worktree/", "git push origin HEAD" push rules)
275→- Any "git worktree add" commands or ".claude/worktrees/" directory references
276→- EnterWorktree tool instructions or worktree-related hooks
277→
278→ADD this section (place it near the top, after any title/intro):
279→## Agent Isolation
280→
281→Teammates run in agentsea sandboxes. Each agent gets a full repo clone with kernel-enforced filesystem isolation. No worktree setup needed.
282→
283→Agents should commit and push on their branch (auto-created by agentsea).
284→
285→KEEP everything else unchanged:
286→- Beads workflow, quality gates, commit conventions, code review rules, etc.
287→- Do not alter content that is unrelated to worktree isolation.
288→
289→Output ONLY the rewritten AGENTS.md content. No commentary, no markdown fences wrapping the output.
290→
291→Here is the current AGENTS.md:`
